27/07/2003
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- The Democratic Union for Integration (DUI) has ordered all party members who hold important administrative positions to give an account of their job performance. According to an article Friday (25 July) in the newspaper <I>Fakti</I>, the members must submit their reports in one month. DUI General Secretary Gezim Ostreni says the party aims to gauge how well its pre-election promises are being implemented. (Fakti - 25/07/03)
